posts.post_content:
This handcut variation was found with a large group of Kotton and Mino-backed t216s and is likely a unique card that was hand cut from a printer's scrap sheet. Blank-backed t216s were not known to exist prior to this find.

Altogether, the card is in GD/VG shape with mild wrinkling and corner wear.  I'm of course, overlooking the irregular hand cut borders however :)

---card is now sold...thanks everyone....
Brian
